{% extends "partials/layout.njk" %}

{% set title = "Accessibility statement" %}

{% block navigation %}{% endblock %}
{% block cookieBanner %}{% endblock %}
{% block backlink %}
    {% from "govuk/components/back-link/macro.njk" import govukBackLink %}
    {{ govukBackLink({
        text: "Back",
        href: params.backLink
    }) }}
{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
        <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
            <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Accessibility statement for Prepare a case for sentence</h1>
            <p class="govuk-body">This page only contains information about the Prepare a case for sentence service,
                available at:
                <a href="https://prepare-case-probation.service.justice.gov.uk/"
                   class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">https://prepare-case-probation.service.justice.gov.uk/</a>
            </p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Using this service</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">This service is run by HMPPS Digital Services. We want as many people as possible to
                be
                able to use this service. </p>
            <p class="govuk-body">For example, that means you should be able to:</p>
            <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
                <li>change colours, contrast levels and fonts</li>
                <li>zoom in up to 200% without the text spilling off the screen</li>
                <li>get from the start of the service to the end using just a keyboard</li>
                <li>listen to the service using a screen reader</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="govuk-body">We’ve also made the text in the service as simple as possible to understand.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body"><a href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/"
                                     class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">AbilityNet</a>
                has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability.</p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How accessible this service is</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">We know some parts of this service are not fully accessible. For example,</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">some documents are in PDF or other non-HTML formats and are not accessible.</p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Feedback and contact information</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">If you have difficulty using this service, email: <a
                        href="mailto:prepareacaseforsentence@digital.justice.gov.uk"
                        class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">prepareacaseforsentence@digital.justice.gov.uk</a>
            </p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Reporting accessibility
                problems with this service</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">We’re always looking to improve the accessibility of this service.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">If you find any problems that are not listed on this page or think we’re not meeting
                accessibility requirements, email: <a href="mailto:prepareacaseforsentence@digital.justice.gov.uk"
                                                      class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">prepareacaseforsentence@digital.justice.gov.uk</a>
            </p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Enforcement procedure</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the
                Public
                Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the
                ‘accessibility
                regulations’).</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">If you’re not happy with how we respond to your complaint, contact <a
                        href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">the
                    Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS).</a></p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Technical information about this service’s accessibility</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">HMPPS Digital Services is committed to making this service accessible, in accordance
                with
                the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.</p>


            <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Compliance status</h3>
            <p class="govuk-body">This service is partially compliant with
                <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">the Web Content
                    Accessibility Guidelines version 2.2 AA standard</a>, due to the non-compliances listed below.</p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Non accessible content</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">The content listed below is non-accessible for the following reasons.</p>


            <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Non-compliance with the
                accessibility regulations</h3>
            <ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
                <li>PDFs and other documents are not accessible in a number of ways including missing text alternatives
                    and
                    missing document structure. This fails
                    <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#non-text-content"
                       class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">WCAG 1.1.1 A (Non-text Content)</a> and
                    <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#page-titled" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">WCAG
                        2.4.2 A (Page Titled)</a>. These documents are automatically extracted from an external service
                    (NDelius) and are not within our control.
                </li>
                <li>The Hearing date column within Outcomes has arrows to sort dates into ascending or descending order, 
                     but screen readers do not make this functionality clear. This fails 
                     <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#non-text-content"
                        class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">WCAG 1.1.1 A (Non-text Content)</a> and
                     <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#info-and-relationships" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">
                     1.3.1 (Info and Relationships)</a>.
                     We are working on fixing this and it should be resolved by December 2026.
                </li>
                <li>The screen reader JAWS may get stuck while the user is browsing Edit my courts. This fails 
                    <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#perceivable"
                        class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">WCAG 2.2 Principle 1: Perceivable</a> and
                    <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#operable" class="govuk-link govuk-link--no-visited-state">
                        WCAG 2.2 Principle 2: Operable</a>.
                    Users can use Tab to navigate to the next item. We are working on fixing this and it should be 
                    resolved by December 2026.
                </li>
                <li>Some of the page titles in the service are not descriptive of the purpose of the page. They are also
                    duplicated in some cases. This fails
                    <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG22/#page-titled">WCAG 2.4.2 Page Titled</a>.
                    We are working on fixing this and it should be resolved by December 2026
                </li>
            </ol>


            <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Disproportionate burden</h3>
            <p class="govuk-body">Not applicable.</p>


            <h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Content
                that’s not within the scope of the accessibility regulations</h3>
            <p class="govuk-body">Not applicable.</p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What we are doing to improve
                accessibility</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">We’ll carry out on-going internal audits to check the accessibility of this service as
                well as taking feedback from users.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">Any required changes will be planned into our continuous improvement work for this
                service.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">This accessibility statement will be updated based on any issues we identify or any
                changes we make to address any issues raised.</p>


            <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Preparation of this
                accessibility statement</h2>
            <p class="govuk-body">This statement was prepared on Wednesday 31 March 2021. 
                It was last reviewed on Thursday 8 January 2026.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body">This service was last tested on Friday 29 April 2022. The test was carried out by
                the Digital Accessibility Centre.</p>
            <p class="govuk-body pac-secondary-text">Last updated: Tuesday 17 February 2026</p>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
